    <h2>Number Series</h2>
    <div class="question">
        <p><strong>Question 1:</strong> What is the next number in the series 2, 6, 12, 20, 30, ...?</p>
        <div class="solution">
            <p>The pattern follows: n(n+1)</p>
            <p>2 = 1×2, 6 = 2×3, 12 = 3×4, 20 = 4×5, 30 = 5×6</p>
            <p>Next term = 6×7 = 42</p>
            <p>Answer: <b>42</b></p>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <h2>Coding-Decoding</h2>
    <div class="question">
        <p><strong>Question 1:</strong> If in a code language, 'MATH' is written as 'NZUI', how is 'LOGIC' written?</p>
        <div class="solution">
            <p>Each letter is replaced by the next one in alphabetical order.</p>
            <p>L → M, O → P, G → H, I → J, C → D</p>
            <p>Answer: <b>MPHJD</b></p>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <h2>Blood Relations</h2>
    <div class="question">
        <p><strong>Question 1:</strong> A is the brother of B. B is the father of C. How is A related to C?</p>
        <div class="solution">
            <p>A is B’s brother, and B is C’s father.</p>
            <p>So, A is the uncle of C.</p>
            <p>Answer: <b>Uncle</b></p>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <h2>Direction Sense</h2>
    <div class="question">
        <p><strong>Question 1:</strong> A person walks 10m north, turns right and walks 5m, then turns right again and walks 10m. What is his final direction?</p>
        <div class="solution">
            <p>The person starts facing north.</p>
            <p>After turning right, he moves east, then right again moves south.</p>
            <p>Final direction: <b>South</b></p>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <h2>Syllogisms</h2>
    <div class="question">
        <p><strong>Question 1:</strong> Statements: All cats are dogs. Some dogs are lions. Conclusion: Some cats are lions. Is it true?</p>
        <div class="solution">
            <p>All cats are dogs, but we don’t know if those dogs are lions.</p>
            <p>The conclusion is not necessarily true.</p>
            <p>Answer: <b>False</b></p>
        </div>
    </div>
    
